@startuml TicketFlow
skinparam maxMessageSize 200
skinparam BoxPadding 10

actor "User\n(Student/Admin)" as User
participant "Browser\n(JavaScript UI)" as UI
database "LocalStorage\n(Browser Vault)" as LS

box "C# Backend (TicketFlowAPI)" #E8F4F8
    participant "ASP.NET\nMiddleware" as Mid
    participant "AuthController" as Auth
    participant "TicketsController" as Tickets
    participant "DatabaseHelper" as DB
end box

database "MySQL Database" as MySQL

== 1. The Login Flow (Getting the ID Card) ==

User -> UI: Clicks "Login" with Credentials
UI -> Auth: POST /api/auth/login\n(Username, Password)
Auth -> DB: ExecuteSelectQuery()\n""SELECT UserID, Role, PasswordHash...""
DB -> MySQL: Execute SQL
MySQL --> DB: Return Results
DB --> Auth: Returns DataTable Row
Auth -> Auth: BCrypt.Verify(Password, Hash)
Auth -> Auth: GenerateJwtToken(Username, Role)
note right of Auth: Creates the 2-hour token\nusing the Secret Key
Auth --> UI: 200 OK\n{ message, token, Role... }
note left of UI: Using the lowercase 'token'\nwe fixed earlier!
UI -> LS: setItem('ticketflow_token', token)
UI --> User: Redirects to Dashboard

== 2. The Secure Request Flow (Showing the ID Card) ==

User -> UI: Opens Dashboard (tickets.html)
UI -> LS: getItem('ticketflow_token')
LS --> UI: Returns JWT String
UI -> Mid: GET /api/tickets/active\nHeader: Authorization: Bearer <token>

note over Mid: Middleware Checks:\n1. Is Signature Valid?\n2. Is Token Expired?\n3. Does User have 'Student' or 'Admin' role?

alt Token is Valid
    Mid -> Tickets: Request Allowed
    Tickets -> DB: ExecuteSelectQuery()\n""SELECT t.*, n.NoteText...""
    DB -> MySQL: Execute SQL
    MySQL --> DB: Return Results
    DB --> Tickets: Returns DataTable
    Tickets --> UI: 200 OK\n[ Array of TicketResponse Objects ]
    UI --> User: Draws Tickets on Screen
else Token Expired / Invalid
    Mid --> UI: 401 Unauthorized
    UI -> LS: removeItem('ticketflow_token')
    UI --> User: Redirects back to Login
end

@enduml